    <details>
      <summary><span class="num">REF</span> Glossary</summary>
      <div class="section-body">
        <table>
          <tr><th>Term</th><th>Plain English</th></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Gradient noise</strong></td><td>Smooth randomness built from random arrows at grid points</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Simplex</strong></td><td>The simplest shape for tiling a space (triangle in 2D)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>fBm</strong></td><td>Fractal Brownian Motion — stacking noise layers for multi-scale detail</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Octave</strong></td><td>One layer of noise in the stack, like one instrument in a band</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Lacunarity</strong></td><td>How quickly we zoom in between octaves (default: 2× each time)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Persistence</strong></td><td>How loud each successive octave is (default: half as loud)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Vector field</strong></td><td>A map that assigns a direction to every point in space</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Curl noise</strong></td><td>Noise field rotated 90° so particles orbit instead of clumping</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Divergence-free</strong></td><td>No pile-ups, no gaps — what flows in must flow out</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Eigenvalue</strong></td><td>Scale factor λ where A·v = λ·v — the "natural frequencies" of a matrix</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Characteristic polynomial</strong></td><td>det(A - λI) = 0 — the polynomial whose roots are eigenvalues</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Complex plane</strong></td><td>2D plane: real part → x, imaginary part → y</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Bohemian matrix</strong></td><td>Matrix with entries from a fixed finite set of integers</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Conjugate pair</strong></td><td>a+bi and a-bi — always appear together for real matrices</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Reaction-diffusion</strong></td><td>System where chemicals react locally and diffuse spatially, producing patterns</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Gray-Scott model</strong></td><td>Two-chemical system with feed (f) and kill (k) parameters</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Turing instability</strong></td><td>Fast inhibitor + slow activator → spontaneous pattern formation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Laplacian (∇²)</strong></td><td>Measures how much a value deviates from its local average</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Autocatalytic</strong></td><td>A reaction where the product promotes its own formation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Ping-pong buffers</strong></td><td>Two alternating arrays so reads and writes don't mix in one step</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Dynamical system</strong></td><td>A system whose state evolves over time by a fixed rule</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Phase space</strong></td><td>The space of all possible states of a system</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Attractor</strong></td><td>A set that nearby trajectories converge toward over time</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Strange attractor</strong></td><td>Attractor with fractal dimension and sensitive dependence (chaos)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Butterfly effect</strong></td><td>Tiny initial differences grow exponentially — deterministic unpredictability</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Fractal dimension</strong></td><td>Non-integer dimension — a curve that's "more than 1D but less than 2D"</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Iterated map</strong></td><td>A dynamical system where each step is a function of the current state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Histogram equalization</strong></td><td>Remapping pixel values to reveal hidden structure in uneven data</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </details>

